On Monday, June 12, 2017 at 12:20 am, a Smith County Sheriffs Office Detention Officer observed an inmate, located in a side cell, hanging from the shower from a ligature. A code blue (medical emergency) was called immediately by jail staff and the inmate was taken down from the ligature. A short time later Tyler Fire personnel and Emergency Medical Services arrived and determined the inmate to be deceased.All proper notifications of jail command staff were made immediately. The Texas Rangers were notified and they proceeded to the scene on the 2nd floor of the Smith County Central Jail. The Texas Rangers, assisted by Smith County Sheriffs Office Crime Scene, documented the scene and contacted the Justice of the Peace. On November 8, 2017, at approximately 1:25 pm, a Smith County Inmate was located by a Detention Officer inside a side cell hanging from a ligature. A Code Blue (medical emergency) was called notifying medical and additional personnel to the area of the jail where the incident occurred. A side cell is a cell designed to house a single inmate. The inmate was cut down from the ligature immediately and Cardio Pulmonary Resuscitation CPR was initiated. Emergency Medical Services and the Tyler Fire Department responded and continued lifesaving efforts. The inmate was transported by EMS to a local hospital where he is listed in very critical condition. The inmate has been in the Smith County Jail since November 2, 2017 and had been in court today.
